item.description:
honors to Kyle Walker per usual, for his handy hack of the ACS package.
Orange County&rsquo;s GINI index as of the American Census Survey&rsquo;s recent 2010-2014 estimates.
{% highlight r %} library(dplyr) library(acs14lite) library(CartoDB) library(rgdal) library(acs) {% endhighlight %}
Set up permissions (get API keys from ACS, CartoDB)
{% highlight r %} set_api_key(&lsquo;zzzzzz&rsquo;) cartodb(&lsquo;username&rsquo;,&lsquo;apikey&rsquo;) {% endhighlight %}
Code
{% highlight r %} acs.lookup(endyear=2014, keyword=&ldquo;Gini&rdquo;) #use ACS package to look up correct table numbers oc&lt;- acs14(geography = &lsquo;tract&rsquo;, variable = c(&lsquo;B19083_001E&rsquo;, &lsquo;B19083_001M&rsquo;), state = &lsquo;CA&rsquo;, county=&lsquo;Orange&rsquo;) oc_tracts &lt;- tracts(&lsquo;CA&rsquo;, &lsquo;Orange County&rsquo;, cb = TRUE) oc2&lt;- oc %&gt;% mutate(geoid = paste0(state, county, tract), gini = round(100 *(B19083_001E),1), moe= round(100 *(B19083_001M),1)) %&gt;% select (geoid, gini, moe) oc_tracts2 &lt;- geo_join(oc_tracts, oc2, &ldquo;GEOID&rdquo;, &ldquo;geoid&rdquo;) r2cartodb(oc_tracts2, &lsquo;oc&rsquo;) {% endhighlight %}
